**AccessOwl: Simplifying SaaS Access Management**

Founded in 2022 and part of Y Combinator Batch S22, AccessOwl is a Berlin-based company focused on streamlining the management of employees' access to Software as a Service (SaaS) applications. The brainchild of Mathias and Philip, both seasoned entrepreneurs with prior startup experience, AccessOwl addresses a growing need for effective access management in a world where remote work and SaaS solutions are proliferating.

### Mission
The mission of AccessOwl is simple: to manage and automate employee access to various SaaS platforms. Initially designed to streamline the provisioning and permissioning of employee accounts, it helps IT teams reduce the average time spent on access requests by 30 minutes per request. This efficiency is crucial as the lines blur between startups and enterprises regarding access management challenges, particularly for organizations pursuing SOC2 certifications.

### The Founders
Mathias and Philip bring a wealth of experience to AccessOwl. Philip previously served as CEO and Co-Founder of Blik, an IoT solution recognized by major players like Volkswagen and BMW. Mathias has a rich background as the Co-Founder and CTO of a leading private payment infrastructure provider in Germany and launched the country’s first digital car insurance. Their collective experiences highlighted the recurring issues in access management that they sought to resolve with AccessOwl.

### Product Overview
Deploying AccessOwl is a breeze — IT can get it up and running in minutes simply by adding a Slack application. The platform supports a range of features including automated user provisioning, access request handling via Slack, vendor management, and SaaS spend management. It eliminates the need for complex integrations like SCIM or SAML, cutting down the time and complexity often associated with identity governance. 

Core functionalities include:
- **Shadow IT Discovery**: Identify every application used within the organization.
- **Access Reviews**: Conduct reviews in minutes instead of weeks.
- **Automated Provisioning**: Streamline user onboarding and offboarding processes.
- **Requests & Approvals**: Facilitate direct access requests and approvals via Slack.
- **Vendor Management**: Centralize all vendor interactions.
- **SaaS Spend Management**: Monitor and optimize software expenditure.

The promise here is saving companies considerable amounts of time and reducing the friction often found in access management workflows.

### Team and Partnerships
With a lean team of four and backing from Y Combinator, AccessOwl is also under the guidance of Group Partner Dalton Caldwell, a notable name in the startup ecosystem. 

### Conclusion
AccessOwl is positioned to be a game-changer in the SaaS access management space, providing essential tools to manage apps, user access, and compliance efficiently. As the landscape of digital business evolves, companies like AccessOwl will be instrumental in helping organizations navigate the complexities of digital security and user management. 

To learn more or get started, visit [AccessOwl's website](https://www.accessowl.io/).

Proprietary AI models such as GPT-4 are very powerful but also very costly, slow, unreliable, and unsecured.

As businesses look to scale their AI prototypes into production-grade products, they struggle with large AI bills, slow APIs and large failure rates.
On the other hand, smaller language models have been proven to be able to perform on-part with large ones with fine-tuned on high-quality datasets.

Airtrain AI lets AI practitioners explore alternatives to proprietary models, build up training datasets, evaluate, fine-tune, and serve a large selection of open-source LLMs.

description:
ALT TEX is a Toronto-based biomaterials startup that has developed the world’s first biodegradable and carbon neutral fabric, engineered from the world’s largest landfill contributor - food waste. Polyester alone makes up 60% of the $2.5 trillion fashion industry and is the biggest blocker preventing brands from meeting sustainability mandates. The patent-pending ALT TEX fermentation technology creates a polyester alternative that works with the existing infrastructure to supply a sustainable, high performance and cost competitive polyester replacement to fashion brands, at scale. 

The product solves key problems for fashion brands, consumers, and the environment:

(1) Fashion brands: ALT TEX sells fabric to fashion brands, allowing them to differentiate via sustainable options (sustainable fashion growing 11% CAGR) and hit sustainability targets, without sacrificing performance or changing their current supply chain.

(2) Consumer: The ALT TEX fabric is projected to be half the price vs. other specialized sustainable alternatives (due to low-cost input and scalability), meaning greater accessibility.

(3) Environment: A single shirt produced with ALT TEX fabric can divert 1 kg of food waste from landfills, 9 kg of carbon emissions from the air, and 4 g of micro-plastics from our waterways.

Co-founders Myra and Avneet have worked together managing teams and projects for six years, with backgrounds in serial entrepreneurship, corporate sales at Fortune 500 companies, textile manufacturing and biochemistry. To date, ALT TEX has created their first fabric prototype that’s 70% stronger than cotton, secured $1M in LOIs and raised $2.3M.

description:
Founded in 2022 and based in San Diego, California, Cisterna Biologics is a technology company. It aims to solve some of the challenges currently facing the biotech industry to develop mRNA-based therapeutics – quality, quantity, longevity and cost of mRNA. As mRNA technology matures, it becomes imperative that these issues are solved so we can fully explore mRNA's endless possibilities as a therapeutic.

Cisterna uses proprietary technologies to either remove a contaminant at its source or replace the source itself. For example, to remove double-stranded RNA (dsRNA), we use ribozymes - molecular scissors - to precisely cut the mRNA at its 3’ end. This assures not only 3’ homogeneity, but also eliminates dsRNA, which are primarily produced due to self-templated additions at the 3’ end. Utilizing a PCR-like system to amplify the DNA template in large quantities eliminates the requirement for plasmid enrichment in bacteria, the prime source of endotoxin contamination. These are just a few examples of Cisterna’s powerful technologies being used to achieve our goal of 10x higher quality mRNA for therapeutic application.

Since then, he has held positions of increasing responsibilities in both academia and industry. He is the author of several publications and industry patents.", 'linkedin': 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/hari-bhaskaran-7697a795/'}]

generated_description:
**Denormalized** is a fresh player in the realm of real-time data processing, birthed from the fertile grounds of Y Combinator Batch S22 in 2022. Nestled in the vibrant tech ecosystem of **San Francisco**, it’s a lean operation with a team of just two. Their mission? To create a **serverless platform** that revolutionizes how developers interact with data.

At its core, Denormalized enables users to query data swiftly without the hassle of complex infrastructure management. The platform shines by automating schema inference from sample data, which significantly boosts developer productivity. Gone are the days when engineers had to grapple with intricate stream processing systems like Flink; instead, they can focus on transforming data using straightforward SQL commands.

So, what sets Denormalized apart? A few key points:

1. **Efficiency and Simplicity**: It’s built on Apache DataFusion, allowing for efficient, in-memory vectorized computation. This means users can process millions of events per second without the burden of managing complicated distributed clusters.

2. **Continuous Compute**: With SlateDB, Denormalized offloads state management to cloud object stores, supporting massive data processing on a single node, making it easier to deploy and maintain.

3. **Reliability**: Users can checkpoint jobs to the cloud, ensuring that processing can seamlessly resume from where it left off.

4. **Performance**: The unique architecture allows for phenomenal speed without the headaches of distributed systems. Developers can create locally and confidently run in production.

Getting started is a breeze—just a simple `pip install denormalized` unlocks the potential for powerful data streaming. Available as both a Python SDK and a Rust crate, the platform invites developers to dive in with minimal overhead, enabling them to move from idea to production in record time.

To explore more about Denormalized, check out their website [here](https://www.denormalized.io/) or read their [Blog](https://www.denormalized.io/blog) and [Docs](https://probably-nothing-labs.github.io/denormalized/denormalized.html) for additional insights.

In a nutshell, Denormalized is all about making **stream processing** accessible for the average developer, saving time and resources while paving the way for innovative data solutions.
headline: serverless platform for real-time data
name: Denormalized

description:
EthosX is a decentralized finance platform creating end-to-end financial derivatives on blockchains. No centralized exchanges, clearinghouses, depositories, clearing banks, CSD participants etc. required.

We are starting with cryptocurrency options first, with the intention to move towards other crypto derivatives and traditional finance derivatives eventually.

For example, one can buy a bitcoin hedging token directly from EthosX without involving any exchange or counterparty and earn profits when the bitcoin price is falling (similar to a put option). It is perpetual and is completely on-chain, end-to-end. It is held as a token in wallets and can be sold/transferred to anyone at any time.

At institutional level, using EthosX’s options infrastructure two hedge funds can trade high-value on-chain options with each other directly without involving any banks or brokers with zero counterparty risk and zero settlement risk.

We are also providing derivatives infrastructure to other crypto companies who want to use these products as a part of a larger package to their customers.

Global derivatives ecosystem is broken. Derivatives trading in traditional finance has way too many gatekeepers and intermediaries. Crypto was supposed to be free of these issues and a solution to all of this, but it is itself getting more and more centralized with disastrous consequences.

We at EthosX intend to pick the best of both worlds and change the way retail and institutional financial derivatives are traded world over.

Additionally, they're building a derivatives infrastructure for other crypto companies, enhancing their offerings without the hassle of extra intermediaries.

### The Problem at Hand

Traditional derivatives trading is bogged down by layers of intermediaries—think exchanges, clearinghouses, banks, and custodians. Conversely, the crypto ecosystem is fast becoming centralized, threatening the very freedom it promised. EthosX believes there's a better way to bridge these two worlds and take back that freedom in derivatives trading, ensuring a transparent, efficient, and user-empowered experience.

### Key Features

- **Direct Market Access**: Users can trade derivatives on assets like BTC, ETH, and various altcoins without intermediaries.
- **Transparent Transactions**: All transactions are clear and straightforward, giving traders confidence over their assets.
- **Real-Time Data & Insights**: EthosX provides advanced analytics tools, helping both retail and institutional traders make informed decisions based on current market conditions.
- **Derivatives RFQ Platform**: Users can easily request quotes for various derivative options, making trading simpler.
- **On-Chain Clearing**: Transactions are streamlined through secure and transparent automated processes.

### Culture and Philosophy

At its core, EthosX is about empowerment—giving traders (both retail and institutional) more control over their trades while simplifying the process. The ethos here is that trading derivatives should not be a labyrinthine process; it should be as straightforward, direct, and risk-aware as possible.

### Community Engagement

EthosX encourages users to join their community, participate in rewards campaigns, and access educational resources designed to improve trading strategies and capabilities. 

**Website**: [EthosX](https://www.ethosx.finance/)  

As the derivatives market continues evolving, EthosX stands at the forefront, advocating for a decentralized future that favors participants, not intermediaries. If you're tired of the convoluted processes and hidden fees in traditional trading, EthosX presents a compelling alternative.
headline: The protocol for derivatives on blockchains
name: EthosX

FlyCode Dunning & Payment Management AI that helps subscription merchants maximize revenue. We reduce passive churn by managing payment failures intelligently.

We’re Jake, Etai, and TD and we’re building FlyCode.

TL;DR: If you sell SaaS or B2C subscriptions, we’re here to help you recover lost revenue due to failed payments and involuntary churn.

‘Involuntary’ or ‘Passive’ churn is a hidden Revenue Killer 💳 for Subscription Businesses

❌ THE PROBLEM: Recovering Failed Payments is Complex
Involuntary churn refers to the loss of subscribers due to payment failures, not due to them actively canceling. While it is both possible and a worthwhile strategy to attempt to win back a customer during the cancellation process — involuntary churn is not intentional and in most cases, your customers aren’t even aware that their payment failed.

💰 Bottom line?
Effective payment optimization does reduce involuntary churn and will increase ARR by as much as 5-10%

FLYCODE SOLUTION 💡
FlyCode leverages ML and AI to provide Payment Optimization and smart payment retries to maximize subscription revenue and reduce churn. We apply a unique model tailored to each Merchant and their customers to ensure optimal results.

⚡️Automatically recover failed subscription payments and reduce passive churn

⚡️Use ML & AI based payment optimization to find the best time to charge your customers

⚡️ Improve customer experience by coordinating payment retries with customer emails/SMS

🛠️ We support OOTB + Custom Integrations for Merchants and White-Label for Platforms

FlyCode was founded in 2021 by Jake, Etai, and TD and is based in Boston. The team is comprised of 7 employees and is part of Y Combinator's Batch S22. Nicolas Dessaigne serves as their Group Partner.

**Mission:**  
FlyCode’s mission is clear: help subscription businesses recover failed payments, thereby boosting retention rates and increasing Lifetime Value (LTV). 

**The Problem:**  
Subscription businesses often face what is known as **involuntary churn**—revenue lost not because customers actively cancel but due to payment failures. This is a significant but often overlooked issue that can be a silent killer of revenue. For many companies, ranging from SaaS to e-commerce, the ability to recover lost payments can lead to a 5-10% increase in Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR).

**The Solution:**  
FlyCode leverages **machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI)** to optimize payment processes and implement smart retry strategies. Here’s how it works:
- **Automated Recovery:** The system automatically retries failed subscription payments, minimizing passive churn without adding to your workload.
- **Intelligent Timing:** FlyCode’s ML models determine the best times to charge customers, enhancing the likelihood of successful payments.
- **Enhanced Customer Engagement:** Coordinated payment retries are coupled with helpful customer communications via email or SMS, improving the overall customer experience.

**Integrations and Reach:**  
FlyCode supports both out-of-the-box and custom integrations, particularly with established platforms like **Stripe** and **Shopify**, allowing merchants to integrate smoothly into their existing systems. They also offer white-label solutions for platforms seeking to enhance their payment management capabilities.

**Recognition:**  
FlyCode was recently recognized as a winner at the **Visa Everywhere Initiative**, showcasing their industry impact and innovative approach to payment management.

**Target Audience:**

**Company Overview: Grai**

Grai is a startup that emerged from Y Combinator Batch S22 in 2021, operating out of San Francisco. At its core, Grai champions open-source version control but with a specific focus: metadata management. The fundamental problem they tackle is the complexity of understanding how database changes might influence machine learning models, APIs, and dashboards—especially when these systems are silos that don’t naturally communicate. This is crucial in today's data-heavy landscape, where knowing the relationships between data points can mean the difference between success and failure for applications and insights. 

**Mission**

Grai’s mission is straightforward: provide an open-source platform for version controlling metadata. This means they offer tools that allow teams to track changes to their data pipelines in a way that anticipates and mitigates issues before they hit production. 

**Current Offerings**

Right now, Grai offers a set of key features that include:

1. **Data Discovery**: This functionality speeds up the process of locating the right datasets. Users can filter and search across their data ecosystems and trace data sources in depth.
  
2. **Advanced Testing**: Perhaps the most critical aspect, this feature automatically tests data changes during continuous integration (CI). It identifies issues before they propagate into production environments, thus maintaining data integrity. 

3. **Developer Focus**: Grai prioritizes community involvement. It's open-source, meaning anyone can contribute and modify it. If your specific stack isn’t supported, you can easily submit a pull request to get it integrated.

**Integration and Community**

Grai is designed to integrate with various tools and platforms—whether on bare metal or cloud environments. Their ecosystem includes a variety of connectors, making it compatible across the board with popular tools such as Metabase, Fivetran, and BigQuery.

Additionally, Grai nurtures a community for developers via a Slack channel where users can discuss features, issues, and best practices, making it a collaborative space for improvement and innovation.

**The Vision Ahead**

The Grai team of three is small but mighty. Their Group Partner, Dalton Caldwell, guides their vision and strategy as they navigate the challenges and opportunities ahead in data engineering and open-source development.

In a data world that's increasingly complex, Grai positions itself as a vital tool that not only helps users understand their data but also equips them to manage it proactively. For those interested in trying it out, Grai offers a free starting point to dive right into its functionalities.

For more information, check out their website at [Grai.io](https://www.grai.io).

description:
Your immune system is your body’s best weapon and defense against cancer. It is only when it is overcome that cancer develops into full blown disease. Dendritic cells sit at the helm of the immune system, directing and dictating immune responses. Data has shown dendritic cells are often dysfunctional in cancer patients, and that this dysfunction is a bottleneck for other therapies. 

Guardian Bio’s approach is focused on creating a dendritic cell-based product which drives anti-tumor activity through activating the killers of the immune system AND training them against multiple cancer targets. We take stem cells from cancer patients, turn them into specific therapeutic dendritic cells specially trained against that patient’s tumor, and re-introduce them back into the body. 

Our therapeutic dendritic cells revitalize the killers of the immune system and give them the kickstart they need to fight - and win - against cancer.

### Guardian Bio: Reinventing Cancer Therapy

**Overview:**  
Guardian Bio is a Boston-based biotech company founded in 2022 that's on a mission to transform cancer therapy using a novel dendritic cell-based platform. The company operates under the belief that the immune system—our body’s most potent defense against cancer—can be enhanced, particularly through the revitalization of dendritic cells. 

**What They Do:**  
Dendritic cells play a critical role in guiding immune responses; however, research shows these cells often become dysfunctional in cancer patients, which can stymie the effectiveness of other treatments. Guardian Bio uniquely addresses this issue by creating tailored therapeutic dendritic cells that are derived from patients' own stem cells. This product not only revitalizes the immune system’s killer cells but also trains them to target multiple cancer types, boosting anti-tumor activity.

**The Technology:**  
Guardian Bio has developed a proprietary process to produce specialized dendritic cells, termed Guard-cDC1s, which effectively restore immune functionality. These cells are pivotal in reinstating antigen presentation capabilities that are often compromised in late-stage cancer. By training these cells against specific tumor targets, Guardian Bio enhances the body’s natural immune responses, making it a promising frontrunner in cancer therapy.

**Team and Education:**  
The founding team includes Ananya Zutshi, who has extensive experience in the biotech sector and education from prestigious institutions such as Duke and Harvard, and Karolina Palucka, a luminary in cancer immunology. Both co-founders are committed to harnessing advanced science to bring innovative solutions to market. The team also includes Richard Barrett, who brings a strong background in immunology and science communication.

description:
Gullak is a mobile app that automates savings & invests these in Gold. We launched in India 60 days ago and have grown from 0 to 40k transacting users and hit a monthly GTV of $280K already. We are growing 25% week on week.

India is a nation of savers but the way the majority of India saves is non-smart & does not create wealth. There are 200 Mn Indians who save manually in bank deposits, the returns from these instruments do not even beat India's inflation. 

Gold is an instrument that India loves - 30Bn worth gold is purchased in India every year by middle income households. Gold has great cultural significance in India & there is high familiarity with the asset class. Despite gold being a familiar asset class & giving 5% higher returns than bank deposits, 200 Mn Indians still save manually in these non wealth creating bank deposits. This is largely because the ways to save in Gold required painful discrete activities such as manually accumulating money to buy gold, going to offline stores to buy this gold, incurring storage charges & more. The minimum ticket size for purchasing gold at these stores is $50 adding to more friction to saving in Gold.

Using automated savings, Gullak now makes it extremely easy for users to save small amounts regularly($1/day) in digital Gold.This was not possible a year ago because the underlying infrastructure(UPI Autopay) was missing. 

With 50 Mn Indians saving $2/day & with gold backed lending, this is a $1.5Bn market opportunity.

Gullak’s Founding team is the team which built BHIM UPI App(10Mn Downloads in 10 Days), this was launched by the PM of India. We built large scale payment systems for partners like GooglePay / Amazon, processing more than 30Mn payments/day. This is the same team that has built more than 40+ consumer brands & their initial growth strategy.

# Gullak Money: An Insight into Automated Savings in Gold

**Gullak Money** is reimagining the way Indians save and invest by leveraging the cultural affinity for gold. Launched just 60 days ago, this fintech start-up has experienced rapid growth, scaling to **40,000 transacting users** and achieving a **monthly Gross Transaction Value (GTV) of $280,000**—and growing at a **25% week-over-week** rate. 

### Mission and Vision

At the core of Gullak's mission is the automation of savings and investing those savings in gold, a cherished asset in India. Currently, around **200 million Indians** save manually in traditional banking options, which often provide returns that hardly keep pace with inflation. Gullak aims to nudge these savers towards smarter, wealth-creating methods.

### The Gold Affinity

Gold purchases in India hit approximately **$30 billion annually**, predominantly from middle-income households. Despite gold's historical performance (typically yielding **5% more** than bank deposits), many individuals remain stuck in less effective savings habits due to the cumbersome nature of acquiring and storing physical gold.

Gullak simplifies this by allowing users to automate small, regular savings (starting at just **$1 a day**) into **digital gold**. This capability only became feasible with the rise of UPI Autopay, which has made recurring transactions seamless.

### Market Potential

With an estimated **50 million Indians** saving $2 daily, and considering gold-backed lending opportunities, the market potential is projected to be around **$1.5 billion**. This presents an exciting horizon for a company like Gullak, which is strategically positioned at the intersection of saving, investing, and the gold market.

### The Team Behind Gullak

The founding team is notable, having previously developed the **BHIM UPI App**, which saw **10 million downloads within 10 days** of launch. This group comes with substantial experience in building large-scale payment systems for leading partners like **Google Pay** and **Amazon**, processing over **30 million payments daily**. They have also been instrumental in creating over **40 consumer brands** in their previous ventures.

### Recent Progress

Founded in **2022** and part of the **Y Combinator Batch S22**, Gullak has quickly built a solid foundation with a dedicated team of **15 employees** based in **Bengaluru, India**. Recently, they secured **INR 10 crore in pre-seed funding** from well-reputed investors like **Better Capital** and **Stellaris Venture Partners**.

### User Experience and Features

Gullak's app is designed to simplify saving, allowing users to:
- Set automatic payments and reminders,
- Invest in **100% secure 24k gold**,
- Save as little as **₹50/day**, 
- Withdraw savings in cash or gold at any time.

Additionally, it includes features such as **daily savings plans**, **gold delivery** options, and opportunities to earn rewards through referrals or special occasions—making the platform not just a savings tool but a rewarding experience.

### Conclusion

Gullak Money is fundamentally changing the way individuals in India save and invest, marrying a time-honored tradition with modern technology. By automating the process and making it user-friendly, they not only provide better returns than traditional savings methods but also empower users to cultivate a more secure financial future in a culturally significant asset class. Interested users can explore more on [Gullak's official website](https://gullak.money).
headline: Gullak automates savings & invests these in gold

### Keylika: Redefining Iron Deficiency Anemia Care

**Company Overview**  
Founded in 2022, Keylika is a burgeoning biopharma startup based in Walnut Creek, California. As part of the Y Combinator Batch S22, the company's mission zeroes in on revolutionizing treatment for iron deficiency anemia (IDA) through innovative metal-based drugs and advanced delivery technologies.

**Innovative Approach**  
Keylika has developed a groundbreaking small molecule iron drug, now formatted as a wearable skin patch, aimed at treating IDA with far greater safety and tolerability compared to existing therapies. This skin patch—the world's first prescription iron patch—delivers iron directly into the bloodstream, steering clear of the gastrointestinal distress often associated with oral supplements, like nausea or constipation. 

**Market Need**  
Iron deficiency is a serious, yet frequently understated condition, impacting around 1.6 billion people globally and over 30 million in the United States alone. Current treatments, such as oral iron supplements, have limited efficacy and poor patient compliance due to their side effects. Intravenous iron infusions might be effective but come with their own risks and costs. Keylika is poised to fill this gap with its proprietary transdermal iron solution, NistuFe, combining the convenience of oral intake with the effective delivery found in IV treatments, minus the downsides.

**Technology Backbone**  
At the heart of Keylika’s technology is a platform synthesis that allows the creation of metal-based drugs optimized for various therapeutic needs. This innovative method not only enhances drug absorption but also reduces systemic toxicity, providing clinicians and patients a much-needed advancement in IDA treatment.

**Leadership**  
The venture is helmed by co-founders Buddhadev P. Chaudhuri and Frederik Ceyssens, both of whom bring extensive expertise in material science, microtechnology, and drug delivery. With a combined 30+ years in research and development, they are committed to ushering in a new era of treatment for iron deficiency.

**Current Status**  
As of now, Keylika operates with a small team, pointing to the agility and focused approach of a startup. Their ongoing work positions them at the closest intersection of medical innovation and practical healthcare delivery, a promising indicator of disruption in a stagnant market.

In summary, Keylika isn't just developing drugs; they're reshaping patient care for millions who silently suffer from iron deficiency anemia. Their innovative, patient-centered solution stands poised to make a significant impact on public health. For more details, visit [Keylika's website](https://www.keylika.com).

**Use Cases**:

- **Automated Permit Preparation**: Streamlines the gathering of various essential documents for maintenance tasks.
- **Faster Troubleshooting**: Helps to quickly resolve operational issues by automating data collection and analysis.

**Industries Served**: Raven is particularly focused on sectors like chemicals, fertilizers, petrochemicals, oil & gas, energy, and utilities.

description:
Relevium Medical is developing an injectable gel for knee osteoarthritis. Approximately half the population will be diagnosed with this pain and progressive disease.
Right now, patients have to undergo not only repeat injections to control their pain, but also have to take strong oral medications. Because the disease is progressive and only gets worse over time, many patients end up on highly addictive, high-dose opioids. 
To date, we have secured $3.7 million in non dilutive funding and completed preclinical testing. We demonstrated that our drug is safe, selectively blocks nerves that transmit pain, and provides pain relief that lasts four times as long. 
Insurance currently pays $770 per six-monthly treatment for knee osteoarthritis. With 5 million patients in the US, this represents a $7.7 Bn market opportunity.
This platform biotherapeutic can also be used to treat other joints affects by osteoarthritis such as the hip and ankle, where the same problems exist in treatment care.

**Company Overview: Signatur Biosciences**

Founded in 2022 as part of the Y Combinator Batch S22, Signatur Biosciences is a London-based biotech startup on a mission to deliver “simple tests for complex diseases.” With a compact team of five, the company aims to revolutionize precision diagnostics, starting with a focus on breast cancer prognosis.

Current diagnostic tests for guiding therapy are notoriously slow and costly. Signatur recognizes that many patients—especially in underserved areas—don't have access to timely, affordable diagnostic tools.

At its core, Signatur Biosciences leverages its innovative **PCRchitectur** technology to streamline and enhance the diagnostic process. Instead of traditional PCR tests that are limited by their need for expensive machinery and lengthy procedures, Signatur's smart PCR kits can be run on standard qPCR machines found in local hospital labs. 

This means a significant reduction in turnaround time from weeks to mere days, enabling faster decision-making in treatment paths. No longer do clinicians have to sift through complex workflows or rely on numerous tests. Signatur’s kits consolidate the work of detecting and interpreting multiple RNA biomarkers into a single test, making the process more efficient and cost-effective.

**A Bigger Vision**

Signatur Biosciences doesn't just see itself as a player in breast cancer prognosis; its ambition is to expand the scope of PCR testing to cover a wider range of diseases, paving the way for smarter healthcare solutions that are both affordable and accessible globally.

In summary, by making precision diagnostics accessible and efficient, Signatur Biosciences stands at the forefront of modern healthcare innovation, potentially reshaping how we think about disease detection and management.

description:
Tailor is a backend platform that helps enterprises build their custom, enterprise grade ERP applications with less code.

**Team**

Yo and Misato have previously built a retail-tech company together and sold it for $20M to Rakuten. Yo is a three-time-acquired serial entrepreneur with a McKinsey background. Misato is a previous head of R&D at Mercari.
Tailor is the first YC company fully based in Japan.

**The Problem**
In today's business world, old ERP systems just don't keep up.

Their monolithic architecture makes it difficult for developers to tailor to the specific needs, even though that's what the enterprises want for ERP. 

At the same time, legacy ERPs struggle to work well with the variety of cloud-based tools that modern businesses rely on.

Legacy, monolithic systems make it very difficult to customize and hard to integrate. Every time the company wants to change something, it becomes a huge project.

Building on these challenges, users of old ERP systems often face:
* Hard-to-Use Interfaces: The screens and menus are old school... confusing, slowing down your work.
* Wrong Set of Features: Too many unnecessary options for you and not enough of what you actually need.
* Lack of Transparency: It's tough to understand what's happening behind the scenes.
* High Cost: The expense of maintaining these systems eats into your budget.

**The Solution**

Why Headless?

- With our headless product, the frontend is easy to customize for clients
- API-first approach makes it easy to connect with other existing systems or 3rd party services

What does it mean to our clients?

- Faster development
- Reduced maintenance cost
- Well-documented backend APIs

Tailor’s key capabilities:

- GraphQL endpoint for flexible frontend development
- Customizable data model templates to describe complex business logic of large enterprises
- Customizable workflows depending on the client's specific business process
- Directory service that can reflect complex organizational structure (e.g. matrix organization) to the workflow

Tailor is transforming the landscape of Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) with its highly customizable headless platform. Founded in 2021 and based in Tokyo, Japan, Tailor emerged from Y Combinator's Batch S22 as the first fully Japan-based startup in the accelerator's history.

### The Problem: Legacy ERPs
In a world where speed and adaptability are paramount, traditional ERP systems simply fall short. Their rigid monolithic architecture is a significant barrier, making it challenging for businesses to customize and integrate the systems with various cloud-based tools. Using outdated ERPs, companies are often bogged down by:
- Clunky interfaces that frustrate users.

- A lack of transparency that complicates issue resolution.
- Exorbitant costs which strain budgets and resources.

### The Solution: A Headless ERP
Enter Tailor's headless ERP model, which allows clients to easily customize the frontend while maintaining a powerful backend. This API-first approach ensures seamless integration with existing systems, enabling businesses to rapidly evolve without the need for extensive overhauls. 

Here’s what Tailor offers:
- **Faster Development**: Custom applications can be developed in days instead of months, thanks to an intuitive customizable platform.
- **Reduced Maintenance Costs**: A well-documented backend and API framework mean less time and money spent on upkeep.
- **Key Capabilities**:
  - GraphQL endpoints for flexible frontend customization.
  - Templates for complex business logic tailored to large enterprises.
  - Workflow management that aligns with specific business processes.
  - A directory service to mirror intricate organizational structures.

### Why Tailor Stands Out
Tailor is built to respond to the complexities of modern enterprises without the headaches of yesteryear's systems. Its commitment to customization aligns perfectly with the needs of businesses looking to streamline operations and accelerate innovation. Importantly, Tailor isn’t just flexible; it’s also secure, with SOC2 certification ensuring that sensitive enterprise data is protected.

### Get Involved
For those ready to ditch their outdated ERP systems and embrace the future, Tailor makes it easy to start customizing an ERP that actually fits your business model. Their platform supports various use cases, making it easier to adapt as your needs change.

**Company Overview: Uwi**

Founded in 2022 and nestled in the bustling city of Singapore, Uwi is on a mission to tackle the housing backlog in Southeast Asia. With their flagship product, the Express Building (EB) loan program, Uwi provides financing solutions tailored for small and medium-sized residential developers in Indonesia and the Philippines. This innovative approach not only aims to ease the burden on the housing market but also to empower developers to scale their affordable housing projects effectively.

Uwi operates in an intricate space that blends fintech with real estate, categorized under various tags like B2B and PropTech. It's worth noting that Uwi is part of Y Combinator’s Batch S22, which speaks volumes about their potential and backing. Their small but mighty team of 14, led by Group Partner Brad Flora, is steadfastly working to refine their approach to financing.

### How It Works

Uwi's Express Building loan is essentially a short-term bridge loan designed to cover the gap between the issuance of official building permits (NOA/LOG) and the eventual bank home loan take-out. Here’s a quick breakdown of the process:
1. **Submission of Business Documents**: Developers kick off by submitting necessary paperwork.
2. **Approval & Post-Approval Requirements**: Once approved, they’ll need to meet additional criteria.
3. **Receive Funds**: Funds are disbursed to the developer.

The EB loan covers 100% of the approved construction budget, with interest-only monthly payments until the principal is repaid at maturity. An important aspect is the flexibility offered with a possible extension of up to 60 days—no prepayment penalties make it even more appealing.

### Current Focus

Uwi is currently laser-focused on Indonesia and the Philippines, two vibrant markets with pressing housing needs. With their innovative financing solutions, they are looking to be a significant player in addressing this shortage.

#### How It Works

3. **Earnings**: This billing structure ensures that landlords can enjoy a consistent income from their solar investments while promoting fair practices—every tenant pays only for what they use.

generated_description:
**Windmill: Turning Scripts into Powerful Internal Applications**

Founded in 2022 and part of Y Combinator's S22 batch, Windmill is a developer-focused open-source platform designed to streamline the creation of internal applications and workflows using minimal code. Based in Paris, France, with a small team of six, Windmill positions itself as a robust alternative to tools like Airplane and Pipedream.

### **Mission and Vision**
The mission of Windmill is straightforward: to provide an open-source platform that facilitates the transformation of simple Python and TypeScript scripts into production-grade multi-step applications. The goal is to empower developers to build, share, and run workflows without getting bogged down by the intricacies of deployment or integration.

### **Core Features**
1. **Seamless Workflow Automation**: Users can sync scripts directly from their GitHub repositories or write them directly within Windmill. The platform automatically converts these scripts into applications and no-code modules, drastically reducing the time from coding to deployment.

2. **Versatile Integration**: Windmill supports a wide array of programming languages, including Python, TypeScript, Go, PHP, Bash, and SQL. This flexibility allows developers to work in their preferred languages and easily manage complex data pipelines.

3. **User-Centric Development**: The platform includes features like auto-generated UIs, webhooks, and an intuitive low-code app editor that employs drag-and-drop functionalities. This makes building complex applications accessible, even to those with limited coding experience.

4. **Community Collaboration**: Leveraging the open-source model, Windmill is building an extensive library of scripts through community contributions, enhancing its capabilities across various APIs and generic tasks.

5. **Self-Hosting and Scalability**: Users can deploy Windmill easily on their own infrastructure or use it as a self-hosted AWS Lambda. It's designed to scale from a single worker to a thousand, accommodating any internal service needs.

### **Use Cases and Adoption**
Windmill is already trusted by over 3,000 organizations, including notable firms like Photoroom, Kahoot, and Bloom Credit. These companies use Windmill to automate back-office tasks, manage complex ETL processes, and streamline their internal operations.

### **Get Involved**
For developers interested in contributing to or using Windmill, they can start building their internal tools in under ten minutes. The robust documentation and community support on platforms like Discord make onboarding smoother and foster collaboration.

### **Conclusion**
Windmill is not just another developer tool; it's a transformative platform that enhances productivity by bridging the gap between code and application in a seamless manner. Whether you're looking to automate workflows or build complex applications with ease, Windmill holds the potential to evolve how developers interact with their scripts.

Explore more about Windmill at [windmill.dev](https://windmill.dev).
headline: Open-source platform to turn scripts into internal apps & workflows
